ct.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-67878675.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-67878675.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20signs%20you%20moved%20on%20too%20soon%20after%20your%20last%20relationship%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Husband%20touching%20wife's%20cheek%20and%20consoling%20her%20at%20home%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65945de81c5c7b8c9a0d5231%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20you're%20keeping%20an%20emotional%20distance%20from%20your%20new%20partner%2C%20you%20could%20be%20unintentionally%20using%20them%20as%20a%20rebound.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%2Ftriloks%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20normal%20to%20seek%20out%20new%20romantic%20connections%20after%20a%20relationship%20breakup.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20certain%20behaviors%20could%20signal%20that%20you're%20in%20a%20rebound%20relationship%2C%20a%20therapist%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20example%2C%20avoiding%20any%20mention%20of%20your%20ex%20could%20suggest%20you%20started%20a%20new%20relationship%20too%20soon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20therapist%20Amelia%20Kelley%20broke%20up%20with%20her%20college%20boyfriend%20and%20longtime%20partner%2C%20she%20adopted%20a%20dog%20to%20fill%20the%20hole%20in%20her%20heart%20%E2%80%94%20and%20her%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20he%20and%20I%20separated%2C%20we'd%20been%20together%20for%20many%20years%2C%20so%20I%20said%20to%20myself%2C%20'I'm%20going%20to%20get%20a%20dog%20so%20that%20I%20have%20a%20warm%20body%20to%20sleep%20with%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20when%20Kelley%20counsels%20her%20newly%20single%20clients%2C%20she%20reminds%20them%20that%20it's%20normal%20to%20want%20to%20fill%20physical%20and%20emotional%20voids%20with%20someone%20new.%20According%20to%20Kelley%2C%20there%20are%20both%20healthy%20and%20unhealthy%20ways%20to%20go%20about%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmy-divorce-rebound-became-my-husband-been-married-7-years-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erebound%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20new%20emotional%20connection%20forged%20following%20soon%20after%20a%20breakup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20rebound%20relationships%20are%20doomed%20to%20fail%2C%20Kelley%20said.%20But%20often%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frebound-relationship-last-therapist-advice-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erebounds%20can%20be%20a%20product%20of%20unprocessed%20emotions%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20previous%20dynamic%20that%20someone%20doesn't%20want%20to%20address%2C%20BI%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20enters%20a%20new%20relationship%20without%20first%20reflecting%20on%20the%20role%20they%20played%20in%20their%20last%20one%2C%20that%20budding%20connection%20will%20likely%20have%20a%20shaky%20foundation%2C%20making%20it%20less%20likely%20to%20last%2C%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20shared%20behaviors%20that%20could%20signal%20that%20you%20dove%20into%20a%20rebound%20relationship%20for%20the%20wrong%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20avoid%20talking%20about%20your%20last%20relationship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20you're%20dating%20someone%20new%2C%20memories%20and%20thoughts%20about%20your%20last%20relationship%20are%20bound%20to%20pop%20into%20your%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20these%20moments%20can%20lead%20to%20helpful%20reflections%20and%20productive%20conversations%20with%20a%20new%20partner%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20find%20yourself%20ruminating%20on%20the%20past%2C%20then%20freezing%20up%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20sharing%20them%20with%20your%20new%20lover%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20sign%20you%20aren't%20ready%20for%20this%20budding%20connection%2C%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can't%20tell%20this%20person%20that%20you%20have%20some%20lingering%20emotions%20you're%20working%20through%2C%20and%20feel%20like%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20them%20to%20yourself%2C%20it%20could%20indicate%20that%20you%20haven't%20done%20the%20work%20to%20process%20your%20breakup%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20constantly%20compare%20your%20new%20partner%20and%20your%20ex%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-heal-from-breakup-when-you-live-with-ex-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalking%20too%20much%20about%20an%20ex%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20also%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20you're%20in%20a%20rebound%20relationship%2C%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20this%20behavior%20could%20suggest%20that%20you're%20focused%20on%20the%20past%20and%20not%20yet%20ready%20to%20nurture%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20keep%20these%20comparisons%20to%20yourself%2C%20fixating%20on%20them%20can%20prevent%20you%20from%20appreciating%20a%20new%20person%20for%20who%20they%20are%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20expecting%20your%20new%20partner%20to%20have%20their%20own%20benefits%2C%20but%20also%20have%20all%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20your%20past%20partner%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20completely%20different%20types%20of%20people%2C%20that's%20not%20fair%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20ignore%20obvious%20signs%20of%20incompatibility%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20breakup%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20consider%20why%20you%20and%20your%20ex%20ended%20things.%20By%20doing%20this%2C%20you%20can%20pinpoint%20signs%20of%20incompatibility%2C%20like%20clashing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthe-3-different-attachment-styles-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunication%20styles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20avoid%20similar%20obstacles%20in%20the%20future%2C%20Kelley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20start%20to%20date%20someone%20who%20is%20so%20different%20from%20your%20ex%20that%20they%20don't%20seem%20to%20align%20with%20your%20typical%20desires%2C%20beliefs%2C%20or%20standards%2C%20it%20could%20mean%20you've%20entered%20a%20rebound%20relationship%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20how%20she%20briefly%20dated%20a%20cigarette%20smoker%20following%20a%20breakup%20with%20her%20longtime%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20repulsed%20by%20the%20smell%20of%20cigarettes%2C%20yet%20he%20was%20my%20rebound.%20Now%20when%20I%20think%20about%20it%2C%20it%20was%20obvious%20that%20I%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20with%20this%20person%20long-term%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20find%20yourself%20gravitating%20toward%20someone%20whose%20lifestyle%20or%20habits%20you'd%20normally%20avoid%2C%20it%20could%20be%20worth%20considering%20why%20you're%20pursuing%20that%20connection%2C%20according%20to%20Kelley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-rebound-relationship-unhealthy-according-therapist-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704323701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65945deeab6f2ebb11f83361%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-rebound-relationship-unhealthy-according-therapist-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20relate%20to%20these%20signs%2C%20chances%20are%20you%20are%20in%20a%20rebound%20relationship.%20A%20therapist%20explains%20how%20to%20spot%20them%20and%20what%20you%20can%20do%20moving%20forward.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnaftulin%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Naftulin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-rebound-relationship-unhealthy-according-therapist-20