mmunicating%20with%20them%20and%20trying%20to%20change%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguirre%20said%20she%20prefers%20using%20%26quot%3Bunhealthy%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20specific%20behavior%20being%20unhealthy%20for%20you%20or%20your%20mental%20health%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20viewing%20a%20full%20person%20as%20irredeemably%20toxic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20rid%20of%20%26quot%3Bgaslight%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20derives%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fculture%2F2017%2F1%2F21%2F14315372%2Fwhat-is-gaslighting-gaslight-movie-ingrid-bergman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E1944%20film%20%26quot%3BGaslight%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20a%20conniving%20husband%20deceives%20his%20wife%20so%20much%20that%20she%20questions%20her%20sanity.%20These%20days%2C%20%26quot%3Bgaslighting%26quot%3B%20has%20become%20quite%20popular%20online%20and%20on%20therapists'%20couches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20totally%20honest%2C%20I%20have%20not%20heard%20a%20person%20use%20it%20correctly%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Morley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20talking%20to%20friends%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65957b5d1c5c7b8c9a0d90f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3Eskynesher%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrue%20gaslighting%20is%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fdomestic-abuse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eabuse%20cycle%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20someone%20is%20making%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20intentional%20effort%20of%20controlling%20and%20manipulating%20the%20other%20person%20by%20denying%20their%20reality%20and%20making%20them%20think%20they're%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20Morley's%20experience%2C%20people%20usually%20use%20%26quot%3Bgaslight%26quot%3B%20to%20mean%20someone%20doesn't%20agree%20with%20them%20or%20their%20reality%20of%20a%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomeone%20can%20just%20not%20understand%20your%20experience%20or%20what%20you're%20going%20through%2C%20and%20that%20lack%20of%20understanding%20is%20not%20'gaslighting%2C'%26quot%3B%20Aguirre%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20she%20said%20if%20someone%20promised%20they'd%20call%20you%20back%20in%20five%20minutes%20and%20waits%20an%20hour%20instead%2C%20they%20might%20genuinely%20not%20understand%20what%20the%20big%20deal%20is%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20intent%20likely%20isn't%20to%20manipulate%20you%20or%20invalidate%20your%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%20being%20honest%20about%20why%20you're%20hurt%2C%20without%20necessarily%20assuming%20someone's%20motives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYour%20ex%20probably%20isn't%20a%20%26quot%3Bnarcissist%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bpsychopath%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPersonality%20disorders%20like%20narcissism%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fdiseases%2F9742-narcissistic-personality-disorder%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eare%20statistically%20rare%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20Morley%20said%20no%20one%2C%20including%20licensed%20professionals%20like%20herself%2C%20can%20diagnose%20someone%20with%20these%20disorders%20outside%20of%20a%20clinical%20setting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20stop%20people%20from%20using%20these%20labels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalling%20somebody%20a%20'narcissist'%20or%20a%20'psychopath'%20cuts%20off%20any%20chance%20of%20doing%20the%20work%20to%20improve%20your%20relationship%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Morley%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20label%20their%20ex%20as%20one%20of%20these%20things%2C%20I%20often%20see%20it%20as%20a%20coping%20strategy.%20We%20would%20all%20love%20to%20think%20that%20our%20ex%20is%20just%20a%20psychopath%20and%20that's%20why%20they%20left%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20she%20said%2C%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdark-triad-vs-light-triad-personality-traits-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epersonality%20disorders%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20exist%20on%20a%20spectrum%2C%20and%20everyone%20is%20capable%20of%20exhibiting%20narcissistic%20or%20sociopathic%20traits%20sometimes%20without%20earning%20a%20formal%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguirre%20prefers%20the%20term%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Femotionally-immature-parent-signs-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemotionally%20immature%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20a%20person's%20lack%20of%20empathy.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20still%20love%20and%20have%20compassion%20for%20those%20people%20who%20are%20emotionally%20immature%2C%20but%20also%20hold%20them%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BBoundaries%26quot%3B%20can%20quickly%20be%20overused%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20boundaries%20is%20important%2C%20said%20Morley%20and%20Aguirre.%20But%20not%20everyone%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esetting%20boundaries%20the%20right%20way%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20might%20use%20%26quot%3Bboundaries%26quot%3B%20to%20cut%20someone%20off%20or%20subtly%20control%20a%20relationship%2C%20Morley%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20terms%20are%20supposed%20to%20help%20you%20figure%20out%20how%20you%20should%20behave%20so%20that%20you%20feel%20good%20in%20your%20life%20and%20in%20your%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20to%20be%20weaponized%20against%20other%20people%20to%20make%20them%20behave%20the%20way%20that%20you%20want%20them%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20listening%20to%20friend%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65957c67ec62ab5daf80448f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EManu%20Vega%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAguirre%20also%20said%20people%20can%20be%20overly%20rigid%20with%20boundaries%2C%20when%20in%20fact%20they%20can%20be%20flexible%20and%20porous.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20a%20parent%2C%20you%20might%20let%20your%20child%20encroach%20on%20your%20need%20for%20space%20and%20quiet%20because%20they're%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20boundaries%20can%20also%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20person.%20You%20might%20be%20OK%20with%20your%20best%20friend%20calling%20you%20at%2011%20p.m.%20with%20an%20emergency%2C%20but%20not%20a%20more%20casual%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20not%20everyone%20knows%20what%20constitutes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Femotionally-immature-parent-set-boundaries-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecrossing%20a%20boundary%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Aguirre%20said%20it's%20better%20to%20set%20expectations%20with%20the%20people%20in%20your%20life.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20of%20a%20conversation%2C%20not%20so%20much%20on%20boundaries%2C%20but%20'What%20do%20we%20expect%20from%20one%20another%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20use%20%26quot%3Btriggered%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Btraumatized%26quot%3B%20for%20everyday%20human%20experiences%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Morley%20and%20Aguirre%20said%20that%20trauma%20and%20triggers%20are%20real%20experiences%20that%20their%20clients%20have%20dealt%20with.%20The%20problem%20is%2C%20many%20people%20are%20using%20these%20words%20too%20broadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Morley%2C%20there's%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20trauma%20and%20%26quot%3Bjust%20normal%2C%20terrible%20human%20experiences%20of%20which%20there%20are%20many%20and%20that%20don't%20dysregulate%20you%20to%20the%20degree%20that%20real%20trauma%20would.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20being%20%26quot%3Btriggered%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20clinical%20sense%20means%20you're%20experiencing%20a%20fight-or-flight%20trauma%20response%2C%20she%20said.%20But%20if%20someone's%20mean%20to%20you%20or%20you're%20going%20through%20something%20difficult%2C%20it%20can%20just%20mean%20you're%20dealing%20with%20uncomfortable%20emotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguirre%20said%20she's%20been%20seeing%20more%20casual%20use%20of%20words%20like%20%26quot%3Btraumatic%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btriggered%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20can%20take%20power%20away%20from%20those%20who%20really%20need%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20she%20started%20using%20words%20like%20%26quot%3Bactivated%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20nervous%20system%20being%20activated%20in%20a%20trauma%20response%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3Btriggered%26quot%3B%20with%20her%20clients%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bit%20helps%20them%20feel%20like%20'I'm%20not%20just%20triggered%20everyone%20else%20says%20they're%20triggered.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BLove%20bomb%26quot%3B%20isn't%20for%20someone%20being%20hot-and-cold%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20gaslighting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Flove-bomb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elove%20bombing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20tactic%20consciously%20used%20by%20abusers%20that%20is%20now%20more%20broadly%20used%20to%20describe%20overwhelming%20enthusiasm%20early%20in%20a%20relationship%2C%20according%20to%20Morley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20love%20bombing%2C%20we%20think%20of%20it%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20overwhelm%20the%20person%20with%20affection%20and%20draw%20them%20in%20so%20that%20they%20don't%20realize%20the%20abusive%20things%20are%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20very%20different%20from%20showing%20intense%20affection%20and%20love%20because%20you%20are%20really%20excited%20about%20somebody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20difference%20is%20that%20real%20love%20bombing%20is%20part%20of%20a%20cycle%2C%20Morley%20said.%20The%20abuser%20consistently%20love%20bombs%20to%20win%20their%20partner%20back%20after%20each%20explosive%20incident%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20in%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20abruptly%20dumped%20by%20someone%20who%20seemed%20obsessed%20with%20you%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20love%20bombing%20to%20be%20painful%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20many%20people%2C%20especially%20when%20they're%20younger%2C%20can%20lay%20it%20on%20too%20thick%20in%20the%20beginning%20before%20they're%20really%20sure%20about%20a%20relationship%2C%20Aguirre%20said.%20They%20might%20just%20not%20have%20the%20maturity%20yet%20to%20go%20slower%20in%20new%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20everything%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bred%20flag%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fred-flags-in-a-relationship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERed%20flags%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20are%20supposed%20to%20identify%20hidden%2C%20harmful%20character%20traits%20in%20people%2C%20such%20as%20narcissism%20or%20abuse.%20But%20Morley%20said%20people%20are%20mostly%20using%20them%20as%20a%20coping%20mechanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222122%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20being%20comforted%20by%20a%20friend%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65957c03ab6f2ebb11f8716e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMStudioImages%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20scanning%20their%20environment%20for%20possible%20threats%20and%20labeling%20red%20flags%20to%20avoid%20engaging%20with%20people%20who%20might%20hurt%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20you%20can't%20do%20that.%20Everyone%20you%20get%20close%20to%20at%20some%20point%20will%20hurt%20you.%26quot%3B%20Plus%2C%20she%20added%2C%20everyone%20has%20moments%20where%20they%20behave%20poorly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAguirre%20said%20that%20red%20flags%20have%20also%20gotten%20more%20unhelpfully%20broad.%20%26quot%3B'Someone%20doesn't%20have%20a%20dog'%20is%20not%20a%20red%20flag%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20First%20off%2C%20it%20doesn't%20actually%20prompt%20you%20to%20examine%20why%20that's%20meaningful%20to%20you.%20Is%20it%20that%20you%20want%20pets%3F%20Or%20that%20the%20person's%20lifestyle%20doesn't%20match%20yours%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20also%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20real%20red%20flag%20because%20it's%20not%20actively%20dangerous%20or%20harmful%20for%20a%20person%20to%20not%20have%20a%20dog.%20Rather%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20would%20be%20a%20non-negotiable%20for%20you%20because%20animals%20are%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BSelf-care%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20mean%20buying%20luxury%20items%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Aguirre%20likes%20the%20idea%20of%20caring%20for%20yourself%2C%20she%20believes%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fself-care-habits-entrepreneur-mental-health-successful-founders-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eself-care%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20can%20be%20misleading%20in%20how%20it's%20presented%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20these%20influencers%20that%20are%20talking%20about%20self-care%20have%20access%20to%20resources%2C%20including%20time%20and%20money%2C%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Aguirre%20said.%20Not%20everyone%20can%20afford%20an%20hour-long%20bubble%20bath%2C%20organic%20food%2C%20or%20even%20professional%20therapy%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Aguirre%20greatly%20prefers%20%26quot%3Bself-compassion%26quot%3B%20instead%2C%20as%20it%20encourages%20%26quot%3Bjust%20being%20kinder%20and%20patient%20with%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20whether%20it's%20%26quot%3Bnot%20going%20to%20the%20yoga%20class%20because%20you%20need%20an%20extra%20hour%20of%20sleep%2C%20or%20not%20beating%20yourself%20up%20because%20you%20didn't%20make%20dinner%20tonight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20every%20behavior%20is%20%26quot%3Bso%20ADHD%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20is%20brimming%20with%20TikToks%20and%20infographics%20about%20real%20disorders%20like%20ADHD%20and%20anxiety.%20But%20Morley%20and%20Aguirre%20both%20warned%20against%20self-diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20diagnosing%20from%20TikTok%20is%20that%20there's%20an%20algorithm%2C%20and%20so%20it's%20information%20to%20show%20yourself%20to%20confirm%20what%20you%20already%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20Morley%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20watch%20five%20ADHD%20videos%20that%20resonate%20with%20you%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20get%2015%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20gets%20extra%20confusing%20because%20%26quot%3Ball%20of%20us%20feel%20like%20we%20have%20ADHD%20to%20a%20certain%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20as%20no%20one%20has%20perfect%20focus%20all%20the%20time.%20It's%20why%20she%20strongly%20encourages%20getting%20a%20formal%20screening%20from%20a%20professional%20if%20you%20suspect%20you%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsymptoms-of-adhd-time-to-see-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EADHD%20symptoms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20many%20symptoms%20also%20overlap%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcommon-adhd-symptoms-that-might-be-something-else-misdiagnosis-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emisdiagnose%20yourself.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Apparent%20autism%20or%20ADHD%20symptoms%20could%20actually%20be%20%26quot%3Brelated%20to%20trauma%20and%20a%20chaotic%20and%20unhealthy%20household%2C%26quot%3B%20Aguirre%20said%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20multiple%20diagnoses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorley%20also%20said%20that%20some%20common%20touted%20symptoms%20of%20ADHD%2C%20like%20having%20sad%20thoughts%20sometimes%20or%20zoning%20out%2C%20can%20be%20universal.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20everyone%20is%20striving%20for%20with%20self-diagnosing%20is%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20live%20an%20easier%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20terrible%20truth%20is%2C%20it's%20just%20incredibly%20hard%20sometimes%20to%20be%20a%20human.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatching%20videos%20and%20slapping%20on%20a%20quick%20label%20can%20feel%20helpful%2C%20but%20it%20can%20actually%20make%20life%20harder.%20%26quot%3BWe%20keep%20trying%20to%20optimize%20our%20lives%20and%20fix%20every%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20whereas%20the%20mindful%20approach%20would%20be%20to%20accept%20our%20flaws%20as%20part%20of%20the%20human%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftherapy-speak-language-terms-retire-2024-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704319262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65957e19ec62ab5daf80455e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftherapy-speak-language-terms-retire-2024-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Therapy%20speak%20has%20become%20popular.%20But%20psychologists%20say%20terms%20like%20%26quot%3Btoxic%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bboundaries%26quot%3B%20are%20being%20misused.%20Here's%20the%20language%20to%20use%20instead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%