0the%20three%20countries%20that%20I%20posited%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20China%2C%20and%20the%20US%2C%20were%20actually%20three%20very%20debated%20relationships%20in%20our%20early%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20referred%20to%20historical%20records%2C%20citing%20exchanges%20of%20notes%20and%20letters%20between%20the%20first%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20Home%20Minister%20of%20India%2C%20Sardar%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%20and%20the%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20Pandit%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20on%20China.%20He%20emphasised%20the%20starkly%20differing%20views%20expressed%20by%20the%20two%20leaders%2C%20shedding%20light%20on%20the%20complexities%20of%20India's%20early%20stance%20on%20its%20relationship%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20something%20which%20is%20my%20fantasy.%20There%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20a%20record%20out%20there.%20There's%20an%20exchange%20of%20notes%2C%20letters%20between%20Sardar%20Patel%20and%20Pandit%20Nehru%20on%20China%2C%20and%20they%20have%20very%20starkly%20differing%20views%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20EAM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20highlighted%20Nehru's%20correspondence%20with%20Chief%20Ministers%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20China's%20place%20in%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%20emphasising%20that%20this%20historical%20context%20provided%20insights%20into%20the%20nuanced%20dynamics%20of%20India's%20diplomatic%20relations.%20%26quot%3BIf%20one%20looks%20at%20even%20the%20whole%20UN%20Security%20Council%20issue%2C%20this%20is%20not%20something%20which%20someone%20is%20saying%20today.%20There%20is%20a%20letter%20which%20Nehru%20has%20written%20to%20Chief%20Ministers%20saying%2C%20first%20let%20China%20take%20its%20place%20in%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20during%20the%201962%20conflict%2C%20Jaishankar%20pointed%20out%20that%20Nehru%20sought%20assistance%20from%20the%20United%20States%2C%20acknowledging%20the%20hesitancy%20in%20seeking%20aid%20during%20a%20time%20when%20India%20was%20under%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%201962%20conflict%20war%20was%20taking%20place%2C%20Nehru%20actually%20wrote%20to%20Kennedy%20saying%2C%20'Look%2C%20I%20need%20your%20help'...I'm%20not%20putting%20his%20exact%20words...but%20more%20or%20less%20'I%20was%20hesitating%20to%20ask%20you%20because%20I%20was%20not%20sure%20how%20it%20would%20look%20overall%20when%20your%20country%20is%20actually%20under%20attack'%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20delved%20into%20the%20ideological%20landscape%20of%20that%20period%2C%20noting%20a%20strong%20left-wing%20influence%20in%20China%20and%20an%20ingrained%20hostility%20towards%20the%20United%20States%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20the%20Americans%20had%20played%20a%20role%20in%20fostering%20that%20hostility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20is%2C%20in%20a%20sense%20there%20is%20a%20certain%2C%20I%20would%20say%20a%20kind%20of%20a%20left%20wing%20ideology%20which%20was%20very%20strong%20in%20that%20period%2C%20in%20China%20and%20similarly%20there's%20very%20ingrained%20hostility%20towards%20the%20United%20States%20the%20Americans%20did%20a%20lot%20to%20deserve%20it.%20But%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20the%20things%20which%20the%20Americans%20did%20we%20probably%20didn't%20deserve%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20issue%20of%20distrust%20towards%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Jaishankar%20referenced%20Sardar%20Patel's%20views%20on%20foreign%20policy%2C%20suggesting%20a%20need%20to%20evaluate%20American%20relations%20based%20on%20India's%20own%20interests%20rather%20than%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20America's%20dealings%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgain%2C%20it's%20an%20interesting%20issue%20where%20one%20of%20the%20last%20comments%20of%20Sardar%20Patel%20on%20foreign%20policy%20was%2C%20why%20are%20we%20sort%20of%20so%20distrustful%20of%20America%3F%20We%20should%20look%20at%20America%20from%20the%20viewpoint%20of%20our%20own%20interest%2C%20not%20from%20the%20viewpoint%20of%20how%20Americans%20are%20dealing%20with%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20EAM%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20ANI%2C%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20that%20India%20should%20deal%20with%20China%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20realism%20and%20asserted%20that%20the%20relationship%20should%20be%20based%20on%20the%20three%20mutual%20understandings--%20respect%2C%20sensitivity%2C%20and%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20also%20reassessed%20India's%20approach%20of%20engaging%20with%20China%20with%20realism%20in%20order%20to%20checkmate%20its%20aggressive%20measures%2C%20while%20also%20hitting%20out%20at%20the%20romanticism%20of%20the%20Nehruvian%20era%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20argue%20for%20dealing%20with%20China%20from%20a%20basis%20of%20realism%20--%20that%20strain%20of%20realism%2C%20which%20I%20feel%20--%20strains%20all%20the%20way%20from%20Sardar%20Patel%20to%20Narendra%20Modi%20--%20that%20is%20the%20strain%20of%20realism%20which%20I%20feel%20should%20allow%20us%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jaishankar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20interview%2C%20the%20EAM%20also%20lauded%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20for%20his%20pragmatic%20approach%20on%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20the%20Modi%20Government%20has%20been%20very%20much%20more%20and%20in%20conformity%20with%20a%20strain%20of%20realism%2C%20which%20originated%20from%20Sardar%20Patel%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20difference%20in%20the%20approach%20of%20India's%20first%20Home%20Minister%20and%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Sardar%20Patel%20and%20first%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20Jaishankar%20highlighted%20the%20difference%20of%20opinion%20among%20the%20two%20stalwarts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20when%20it%20came%2C%20for%20example%20to%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20seat%2C%20it's%20not%20my%20case%20that%20we%20should%20have%20necessarily%20taken%20the%20seat%2C%20it's%20a%20different%20debate%2C%20but%20to%20say%20that%20we%20should%20first%20let%20China%20--%20China's%20interest%20should%20come%20first%2C%20it's%20a%20very%20peculiar%20statement%20to%20make%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jaishankar%20while%20dealing%20with%20the%20approach%20of%20Nehru%20and%20Sardar%20Patel's%20realism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20into%20Nehru's%20tenure%2C%20Sino-Indian%20relations%20were%20characterised%20by%20what%20was%20perceived%20as%20friendship%20and%20cordiality%20that%20covered%20both%20bilateral%20and%20regional%20and%20international%20issues%3B%20however%2C%20India%20got%20a%20rude%20awakening%20when%20China%20launched%20a%20war%20in%201962%20that%20gave%20decision%20makers%20in%20New%20Delhi%20a%20reality%20check%20on%20their%20China%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20two%20hands%20to%20clap.%20I%20pose%20the%20issue%20in%20this%20manner%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20last%2075%20plus%20years%20of%20our%20foreign%20policy%2C%20they%20have%20a%20strain%20of%20realism%20about%20China%20and%20have%20a%20strain%20of%20idealism%2C%20romanticism%2C%20non-realism.%20It%20begins%20right%20from%20day%20one%2C%20there%20is%20a%20sharp%20difference%20of%20opinion%20--%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20China%20between%20Nehru%20and%20Sardar%20Patel%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jaishankar%20while%20responding%20to%20a%20question%20on%20whether%20the%20two%20nations%20will%20bury%20the%20hatchet%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704303540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fp72b4dgg_s-jaishank