3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%2C%20filed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20reporter%20Sukanya%20Shantha%2C%20came%20up%20for%20its%20first%20hearing%20today%20before%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20division%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20issued%20notice%20to%2011%20states%20where%20the%20prison%20rule-sanctioned%20practice%20continues%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%20and%20the%20academy%20of%20prisons%20and%20correctional%20administration%20in%20Vellore%2C%20and%20sought%20responses%20within%20four%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20noted%20that%20the%20petition%20raises%20some%20%E2%80%9Cimportant%20issues%E2%80%9D%20and%20took%20note%20of%20the%20points%20raised%20by%20senior%20advocate%20S.%20Muralidhar%2C%20who%20is%20representing%20Sukanya%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20was%20filed%20through%20advocate-on-record%20S.%20Prasanna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20took%20note%20of%20three%20aspects%20in%20which%20discrimination%20is%20prevalent%20in%20prisons.%20The%20first%20is%20the%20division%20of%20labour%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste.%20The%20second%20is%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20segregation%20of%20prisoners%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20caste%2C%20and%20the%20third%20is%20the%20discriminatory%20provisions%20used%20specifically%20against%20the%20Denotified%20Tribes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20also%20called%20upon%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20who%20was%20also%20present%2C%20to%20assist%20the%20court%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%2C%20who%20claimed%20to%20be%20unaware%20of%20the%20practice%2C%20described%20it%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D%20and%20told%20the%20court%20he%20would%20work%20with%20Muralidhar%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Findia-prisons-caste-labour-segregation%5C%22%3EFrom%20Segregation%20to%20Labour%2C%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20Caste%20Law%20Governs%20the%20Indian%20Prison%20System%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20noted%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20work%20%E2%80%98From%20Segregation%20to%20Labour%2C%20Manu%E2%80%99s%20Caste%20Law%20Governs%20the%20Indian%20Prison%20System%E2%80%99%20that%20became%20the%20basis%20for%20this%20petition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20was%20produced%20as%20part%20of%20a%20five-part%20prison%20series%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpulitzercenter.org%2Fprojects%2Fbarred-prisons-project%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EBarred%E2%80%93The%20Prisons%20Project%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Sukanya%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20deputy%20editor%20Jahnavi%20Sen%20had%20produced%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Pulitzer%20Center%20for%20Crisis%20Reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20series%20has%20won%20several%20awards%20both%20in%20India%20and%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrisons%20are%20a%20state%20subject%20and%20are%20run%20as%20per%20the%20prison%20manuals%20of%20individual%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20prison%20manuals%20have%20gone%20through%20a%20few%20changes%20in%20the%20past%20decades%2C%20some%20continue%20to%20retain%20unconstitutional%20caste-based%20labour%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20prison%20manual%20of%201968%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9Cconservancy%20work%2C%20or%20manual%20scavenging%2C%20shall%20be%20carried%20out%20by%20a%20Mehtar%20prisoner%20who%20would%20be%20assigned%20for%20handling%20human%20excreta%20in%20the%20toilets%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehtars%20are%20a%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20have%20for%20long%20engaged%20in%20manual%20scavenging%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20along%20with%20assigning%20sweeping%20work%20to%20those%20from%20Dalit%20community%2C%20the%20West%20Bengal%20jail%20code%20also%20states%20that%20those%20belonging%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20caste%E2%80%9D%20group%20shall%20be%20appointed%20as%20cooks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20story%20was%20published%20in%20December%202020%2C%20the%20Jodhpur%20bench%20of%20the%20Rajasthan%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcaste-prison-rajasthan-high-court-prison-manual-suo-motu%5C%22%3Ehad%20%3Cem%3Esuo%20motu%3C%2Fem%3E%20taken%20the%20case%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20directed%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20home%20department%20to%20change%20its%20prison%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%2070%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Frajasthan-prison-manual-amended-caste-labour%5C%22%3Ethe%20rule%20book%20was%20finally%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20all%20mentions%20of%20caste-based%20practices%20were%20finally%20dropped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpulitzercenter.org%2Fstories%2Fmisgendering-sexual-violence-harassment-what-it-be-transgender-person-indian-prison%5C%22%3EMisgendering%2C%20Sexual%20Violence%2C%20Harassment%3A%20What%20it%20Is%20to%20Be%20a%20Transgender%20Person%20in%20an%20Indian%20Prison%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20replicated%20in%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20story%20covered%20in%202020%2C%20Sukanya%2C%20along%20with%20lawyer%20and%20anti-caste%20scholar%20Disha%20Wadekar%2C%20further%20looked%20at%20problematic%20aspects%20in%20the%20prison%20manuals%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Model%20Prison%20Manual%20that%20most%20states%20have%20slowly%20begun%20adopting%20was%20also%20studied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20found%20that%20along%20with%20caste%20segregation%2C%20the%20prison%20manuals%20also%20sanction%20a%20discriminatory%20approach%20towards%20the%20Denotified%20Tribes.%20These%20communities%2C%20who%20have%20for%20long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1032031%2Fcitizens-without-citizenship-how-true-freedom-still-eludes-indias-denotified-nomadic-tribes%5C%22%3Efaced%20criminalisation%20just%20by%20virtue%20of%20their%20birth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20exempted%20from%20the%20most%20basic%20rights%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuralidhar%20pointed%20out%20to%20the%20court%20that%20they%20have%20long%20faced%20discrimination%20in%20society%20and%20their%20ill-treatment%20continues%20even%20when%20they%20go%20to%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20accessing%20prison%20manuals%20%E2%80%93%20documents%20that%20most%20states%20have%20kept%20away%20from%20both%20prisoners%20and%20their%20lawyers%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20story%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20physical%20segregation%20of%20prisoners%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste%20in%20the%20Palayamkottai%20central%20prison%20in%20Tirunelveli.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20prisoners%20are%20assigned%20barracks%20as%20per%20their%20caste.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20prisoner%20belonging%20to%20the%20dominant%20Thevar%20caste%20would%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CThevar%20barrack%E2%80%9D%20and%20one%20from%20the%20Pallar%20caste%20(a%20Scheduled%20Caste)%20will%20be%20assigned%20a%20different%20barrack%20meant%20for%20that%20specific%20caste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20when%20petitioner%20C.%20Arul%20moved%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20home%20department%20justified%20the%20segregation%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20essential%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprevent%20caste%20rivalries%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20too%20had%20accepted%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20petition%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20too%20has%20been%20challenged.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704290919000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-cont