%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVanashakti%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20EIA%20mandates%20prior%20approval%20before%20the%20start%20of%20any%20activity%2C%20and%20allowing%20ex%20post%20facto%20environmental%20clearance%20is%20%E2%80%9Canathema%20to%20the%20Environment%20Protection%20Act%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESankaranarayanan%20argued%20further%20that%20the%20EIA%20notification%20of%202006%20mandates%20prior%20environment%20clearance%20for%20all%20projects%20and%20the%20problem%20began%20with%20an%20office%20memorandum%20of%202017%20which%20provided%20a%20six-month%20window%20for%20alleged%20violators%20to%20apply%20for%20post%20facto%20clearance.%20To%20further%20his%20case%2C%20Sankaranarayanan%20cited%20previous%20Supreme%20Court%20orders%20which%20sought%20to%20balance%20the%20twin%20goals%20of%20sustainable%20development%20and%20environmental%20protection%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnon-derogable%E2%80%9D%20requirement%20under%20the%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fsc-stays-ex-post-facto-mining-clearance-without-prior-environmental-clearance-101704252518222.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704279644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F04%2F15182007%2FCoal-mining-Maharashtra-%2540-Ashish-Kothari-copy.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-centres-orders-on-ex-post-facto-environmental-clearance-for-mining-projects%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20imposed%20stay%20on%20MoEF's%20July%202021%20and%20January%202022%20orders%2C%20which%20granted%20permission%20for%20ex-post%20facto%20clearance%20without%20prior%20approval%20mandated%20under%20the%20Environment%20Impact%20Assessment%20notification%20of%202006.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22