20the%20superficially%20laudatory%20articles%20in%20the%20foreign%20media.%20Meanwhile%2C%20foreign%20financiers%20lend%20to%20the%20country%20willingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%2C%20of%20course%2C%20things%20change.%20And%20they%20change%20rather%20quickly.%20All%20those%20things%20that%20were%20glossed%20over%20previously%20suddenly%20loom%20large.%20Turns%20out%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20banks%20are%20saddled%20with%20bad%20loans%20issued%20to%20politically%20connected%20cronies%20and%20crooks.%20The%20currency%20tanks.%20Inflation%20soars.%20With%20peaceful%20democratic%20avenues%20closed%2C%20a%20spasm%20of%20violence%20ensues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%2C%20banking%20sector%20woes%2C%20and%20authoritarian%20politics%20make%20for%20a%20volatile%20cocktail%20that%20is%20redolent%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%20of%20the%20mid-1990s%20%E2%80%93%20but%20as%20things%20stand%2C%20they%20also%20describe%20a%20Bangladesh%20of%20the%20mid-2020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20consider%20each%20of%20these%20elements%20in%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Bangladesh%20has%20become%20a%20capital%20importer%2C%20running%20a%20current%20account%20deficit%20even%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20And%2C%20according%20to%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20(IMF%E2%80%99s)%20latest%20assessment%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20the%20deficit%20is%20likely%20to%20persist%20well%20into%20the%20late%202020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20nation%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20reflects%20the%20difference%20between%20its%20aggregate%20savings%20and%20investment%2C%20with%20a%20deficit%20signifying%20inadequate%20savings%20to%20meet%20its%20investment%20needs.%20With%20around%2030%25%20of%20GDP%20saved%2C%20the%20savings%20rate%20in%20Bangladesh%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20low%20%E2%80%93%20by%20way%20of%20comparison%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20savings%20rate%20has%20tended%20to%20be%20around%2015%25%20of%20GDP.%20Rather%2C%20as%20Chart%201%20shows%2C%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20current%20account%20deficit%20reflects%20a%20strong%20investment%20boom%20before%20the%20pandemic%20that%20is%20set%20to%20resume%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22929%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2.jpg%20929w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121207%2FChart-1-and-2-300x186.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691395%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22575%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20Chart%202%20shows%20that%20while%20private%20investment%20is%20set%20to%20recover%20to%20the%20pre-pandemic%20levels%20relative%20to%20GDP%2C%20shaking%20off%20recent%20woes%2C%20public%20investment%20is%20projected%20to%20scale%20new%20heights%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%20Of%20course%2C%20in%20and%20of%20itself%2C%20this%20is%20very%20sensible.%20Bangladesh%20is%20a%20developing%20country%20desperately%20in%20need%20of%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20roads%2C%20railways%2C%20electricity%20generation%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20There%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20financing%20some%20of%20these%20projects%20from%20external%20sources%2C%20provided%20the%20projects%20are%20well%20governed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20elements%20to%20this.%20First%2C%20financing%20of%20many%20of%20these%20projects%20is%20quite%20one-sided%20against%20Bangladeshi%20taxpayers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froadtodemocracy.com%2F2023%2F03%2F20%2Fadani-group-awami-league-nexus%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20power%20purchase%20agreement%20with%20the%20Adani%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20a%20particularly%20egregious%2C%20but%20far%20from%20the%20only%2C%20example.%20Second%2C%20these%20projects%20are%20usually%20implemented%20with%20woeful%20management%2C%20resulting%20in%20significant%20cost%20overruns.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbdnews24.com%2Feconomy%2Fbangladesh-infrastructure-is-worlds-costliest-says-world-bank%5C%22%3Einfrastructure%20projects%20were%20among%20the%20costliest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20persistent%20current%20account%20deficit%20may%20well%20have%20an%20upside%20to%20it%2C%20at%20least%20theoretically%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20positive%20about%20a%20wobbly%20banking%20sector.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20banking%20sector%20is%20saddled%20with%20non-performing%20loans%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20borrower%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20interest%20or%20principal%20payments%20for%20an%20extended%20period.%20Chart%203%20shows%20that%20the%20problem%20is%20particularly%20acute%20in%20the%20state-owned%20banks%2C%20which%20are%20also%20not%20well%20capitalised%20(Chart%204)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20they%20are%20not%20well%20placed%20to%20cover%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20their%20lending.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22951%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4.jpg%20951w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121545%2FChart-3-and-4-300x179.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691397%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22567%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20governance%20problems%20around%20the%20infrastructure%20megaprojects%20as%20well%20as%20the%20woes%20in%20the%20banking%20sector%20ultimately%20point%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20authoritarian%20political%20economy%20whereby%20the%20ruling%20regime%2C%20instead%20of%20governing%20with%20a%20mandate%20from%20the%20voters%2C%20has%20been%20relying%20on%20the%20support%20of%20powerful%20oligarchs%20who%20are%20given%20access%20to%20loans%20and%20opportunities%20without%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChart%205%20shows%20the%20regression%20of%20electoral%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20using%20the%20V-Dem%20index.%20This%20index%20captures%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20governments%20are%20elected%20under%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20with%20guaranteed%20freedom%20of%20association%20and%20expression.%20Countries%20are%20given%20a%20score%20between%200%20and%201%2C%20the%20latter%20being%20most%20democratic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Bangladesh%20had%20a%20score%20of%200.27%2C%20compared%20with%200.4%20in%20India%20and%200.39%20in%20Pakistan.%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20slide%20to%20authoritarianism%20reflects%20a%20one-sided%20election%20in%20January%202014%20where%20the%20incumbent%20Awami%20League%20won%20153%20seats%20out%20of%20300%20unopposed%2C%20and%20a%20blatantly%20rigged%20election%20in%20December%202018%20when%20ballot%20boxes%20were%20stuffed%20the%20night%20before%20the%20polling%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22857%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5.jpg%20857w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03121937%2FChart-5-300x164.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691399%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%E2%80%99s%20turn%20towards%20a%20dictatorship%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20third%20consecutive%20one-sided%20election%20on%20January%207%20%E2%80%93%20the%20opposition%20parties%20are%20boycotting%20the%20election%20in%20light%20of%20their%20past%20experience%20as%20well%20as%20the%20fact%20that%20over%2020%2C000%20of%20their%20members%20have%20been%20interned%20since%20late%20October%20through%20a%20draconian%20crackdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20may%20look%20unassailable%20politically.%20But%20so%20did%20President%20Suharto%20of%20Indonesia%20in%201996.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20nostrum%20pushed%20by%20authoritarian%20leaders%20that%20they%20can%20make%20the%20tough%20decisions%20needed%20to%20address%20economic%20challenges%2C%20experiences%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20(and%20indeed%20in%20many%20other%20countries%20around%20the%20world)%20suggest%20that%20authoritarian%20regimes%20with%20poorly%20governed%20banking%20sectors%20and%20mega%20projects%20often%20end%20up%20in%20significant%20political%20and%20economic%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20making%20tough%20decisions%20and%20taking%20on%20the%20vested%20interests%2C%20authoritarian%20regimes%20relied%20on%20the%20very%20same%20vested%20interests%20for%20their%20survival.%20The%20resulting%20cronyism%20only%20exacerbated%20the%20crisis%2C%20not%20resolved%20it.%20In%20Thailand%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Asian%20Financial%20Crisis%20of%201997%20was%20followed%20by%20years%20of%20political%20conflict%20and%20economic%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%2C%20of%20course%2C%20has%20been%20experiencing%20considerable%20economic%20difficulty%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20with%20the%20taka%20depreciating%20by%20over%2040%25%20against%20the%20US%20dollar%20despite%20the%20central%20bank%20burning%20through%20about%20half%20of%20its%20international%20reserves%20while%20inflation%20remained%20at%20double%20digits.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20noxious%20politics%20and%20unsound%20economic%20fundamentals%20make%20for%20a%20very%20combustible%20brew%20that%20could%20spill%20over%20beyond%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJyoti%20Rahman%20is%20a%20Bangladeshi%20economist.%20His%20analyses%20are%20archived%20at%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjrahman.substack.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fjrahman.substack.com%2F%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20he%20can%20be%20contacted%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3AJyoti.rahman%40gmail.com%5C%22%3EJyoti.rahman%40gmail.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704273025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03144455%2FEffect-52.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fdespite-political-repression-economic-crisis-bangladesh-is-set-for-a-one-sided-election-on-jan-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20opposition%20parties%20boycotting%20the%20election%20and%20mass%20arrests%2C%20Bangladesh's%20turn%20towards%20a%20dictatorship%20under%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20is%20set%20to%20continue%20with%20the%20third%20consecutive%20one-sided%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fdespite-political-repression-economic-crisis-bangladesh-is-set-for-a-one-sided-election-on-jan-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saleh%20al%20Arouri%3A%20Who%20was%20the%20deputy%20Hamas%20leader%20killed%20in%20Beirut%20explosion%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704272880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-saleh-al-arouri-hamas_6410933.jpg%3F20240103130850%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsaleh-al-arouri-who-was-the-deputy-hamas-leader-killed-in-beirut-explosion-13041360%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20am%20living%20on%20borrowed%20time%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0Saleh%20al%20Arouri%20said%20in%20August.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20waiting%20for%20martyrdom%20and%20think%20that%20I%20lived%20too%20long.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsaleh-al-arouri-who-was-the-deputy-hamas-leader-killed-in-beirut-explosion-13041360%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsaleh-al-arouri-who-was-the-deputy-hamas-leader-killed-in-beirut-explosion-13041360%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsaleh-al-arouri-who-was-the-deputy-hamas-leader-killed-in-beirut-explosion-13041360%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Seeks%20Reply%20From%20LS%20Secretariat%20Over%20Mahua%20Moitra's%20Ouster%2C%20'MP%20Can't%20Attend%20as%20Interim%20Measure'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F07170726%2F2022_4img04_Apr_2022_PTI04_04_2022_000155B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20issued%20notice%20to%20the%20secretary%20general%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20plea%20challenging%20her%20recent%20expulsion%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Dipankar%20Datta%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20the%20court%20will%20be%20looking%20at%20is%20if%20the%20court%20has%20the%20jurisdiction%20to%20review%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-mahua-moitra-expulsion-lok-sabha-unethical-conduct-cash-for-query-allegations-245741%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20appeared%20to%20oppose%20this%20line%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20sovereign%20organ%20of%20the%20State%20is%20deciding%20its%20internal%20discipline.%20What%20is%20the%20scope%20of%20judicial%20review%2C%20if%20at%20all%3F%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20said%20that%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%E2%80%99s%20reply%20is%20to%20be%20filed%20within%20three%20weeks.%20Moitra%20will%20get%20an%20additional%20three%20weeks%20to%20file%20a%20rejoinder%2C%20if%20any.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Advocate%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20who%20is%20counsel%20for%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20pleaded%20with%20the%20court%20that%20Moitra%20be%20allowed%20to%20attend%20Lok%20Sabha%20proceedings%20in%20the%20meantime%20as%20an%20interim%20measure.%20The%20court%20did%20not%20grant%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoitra%20is%20lawmaker%20from%20Krishnanagar%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20On%20December%208%2C%20she%20was%20expelled%20after%20an%20ethics%20committee%20report%20accused%20her%20of%20unethical%20conduct%20over%20a%20cash-for-query%20allegations%20against%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chairperson%20of%20the%20committee%20is%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20MP%20Vinod%20Kumar%20Sonkar.%20Moitra%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3Eslammed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20probe%20as%20%E2%80%98filthy%2C%20unethical%2C%20misogynistic%E2%80%99.%20Several%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20walked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20came%20after%20BJP%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%20along%20with%20a%20lawyer%2C%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20%E2%80%93%20termed%20by%20Moitra%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98jilted%20ex%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20had%20filed%20the%20complaint%20with%20the%20committee%20alleging%20that%20the%20TMC%20MP%20had%20accepted%20bribes%20from%20Dubai-based%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20parliament.%20The%20complaint%20said%20Moitra%20had%20shared%20the%20password%20of%20the%20official%20email%20of%20her%20Lok%20Sabha%20account%20with%20Hiranandani%2C%20claiming%20it%20had%20compromised%20%E2%80%98national%20security%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Singhvi%20in%20court%20cited%20what%20was%20standard%20practice%20for%20MPs%20%E2%80%93%20to%20delegate%20work%20to%20secretaries%20and%20assistants%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20uploading%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCan%20an%20MP%20not%20delegate%20her%20work%3F%20Imagine%20Hiranandani%20to%20be%20her%20secretary%20for%20a%20minute.%20Now%20you%20can%20say%20that%20he%20is%20not%20her%20secretary%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20asked%20him%20if%20he%20is%20accepting%20that%20a%20one-time%20password%20was%20shared%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704271518000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F07170726%2F2022_4img04_Apr_2022_PTI04_04_2022_000155B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-lok-sabha-secretariat-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20apex%20court%20said%20that%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general's%20reply%20is%20to%20be%20filed%20within%20three%20weeks.%20Moitra%20will%20get%20an%20additional%20three%20weeks%20to%20file%20a%20rejoinder%2C%20if%20any.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-lok-sabha-secretariat-mahua-moitra%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trucker%20Protests%20Are%20Another%20Instance%20of%20the%20Success%20of%20Street%20Politics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03132615%2FDM1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truck-drivers%E2%80%99%20associations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fnationwide-truckers-protest-maharashta-mp-gujarat-9091384%2F%