-farmers-protest-a-triumph-of-satyagraha-politics%5C%22%3Eanatomical%20diagnosis%20of%20this%20civil%20resistance%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20our%20understanding%2C%20was%20shaped%20by%20the%20perseverance%20of%20those%20imbibing%20the%20cultural%20ethos%20of%20Sikh%20tradition%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1010957%2Fanalysis-in-modis-repeal-of-the-contentious-farm-laws-a-triumph-of-the-power-of-collective-action%5C%22%3E%2C%C2%A0with%20an%20undistilled%20faith%20in%20the%20collective%20public%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20Satyagraha%20methods%20of%20protest.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20andolan%E2%80%99s%20success%20renewed%20one%E2%80%99s%20faith%20in%20the%20patient-perseverant%20success%20of%20Satyagraha%20politics%2C%20even%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03133448%2FDM2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03133448%2FDM2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03133448%2FDM2-300x198.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03133448%2FDM2-1024x677.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691420%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22793%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Jignesh%20Mistry%2C%20CNES%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fin-photos-remembering-the-farmers-protest-a-triumph-of-satyagraha-politics%5C%22%3Eandolan%20was%20called%20a%20Satyagraha%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20most%20protestors%20and%20union%20activists%20we%20spoke%20to%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ESatyagraha%2C%20characterised%20by%20a%20non-violent%20form%20of%20protest%2C%20civil%20disobedience%20and%20non-cooperation%2C%20has%20been%20embedded%20in%20the%20fabric%20of%20Indian%20agrarian%20movements%20from%20much%20before%20independence.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.com%2Fstable%2F44257393%5C%22%3ESatyagraha%C2%A0method%C2%A0of%20mass%20mobilisation%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20non-cooperation%20movement%20had%20put%20tremendous%20political%20and%20economic%20pressure%20on%20the%20British%20Raj%20through%20the%20boycott%20of%20foreign%20goods%20and%20picketing%20of%20shops%20before%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%20the%20Kisan%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAndolan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20parallels%20were%20drawn%20between%20the%20Raj%20and%20Modi%20government-even%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmodi-governmentality-similar-to-british-raj-s-755088.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20introduction%20of%20codified%20Labor%20Laws%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20without%20due%20consultation%20with%20unions%20and%20worker-groups%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmodi-governmentality-similar-to-british-raj-s-755088.html%5C%22%3Esimilarities%20between%20the%20Modi%20Government%20and%20an%20colonial%20oppressor%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20protestor%20from%20Ludhiana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fin-photos-remembering-the-farmers-protest-a-triumph-of-satyagraha-politics%5C%22%3Ewho%20we%20spoke%20to%20during%20our%20field%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Kisan%20Andolan%2C%20said%20that%20in%20villages%20of%20Punjab%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20have%20now%20started%20boycotting%20goods%20from%20firms%20behind%20commercialisation%20and%20privatisation%2C%20such%20as%20petrol%20and%20mobile%20network%20services%20from%20the%20Mukesh%20Ambani-led%20Reliance%20Industries%20Limited%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20other%20most%20important%20features%20of%20the%20Kisan%20Andolan%C2%A0was%20the%20cooperation%20received%20from%20people%20belonging%20to%20different%20demographics%2C%20particularly%20the%20youth%20and%20women%2C%20within%20the%20farming%20and%20non-farming%20rural%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20youth%20played%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20sustaining%20and%20monitoring%20movement.%20While%20they%20made%20sure%20that%20only%20those%20having%20an%20identity%20card%20entered%20the%20site%20and%20stood%20guard%20outside%20tents%20of%20women%2C%20their%20most%20important%20duty%20was%20to%20coordinate%20social%20media%20and%20communication.%20They%20ran%20social%20media%20campaigns%20and%20streamed%20the%20speeches%20spoken%20on%20stage%20live%20through%20social%20media%20handles%2C%20such%20as%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03134258%2FDM3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03134258%2FDM3.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03134258%2FDM3-300x197.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03134258%2FDM3-1024x673.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691421%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22789%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Jignesh%20Mistry%2C%20CNES%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElderly%20women%20were%20driving%20tractors%2C%20participating%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Elangar%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0kitchens%20and%20delivering%20speeches%20on%20stage.%20If%20not%20at%20the%20protest%20sites%2C%20women%20(and%20also%20children)%20tended%20to%20fields%20and%20managed%20households%20back%20in%20the%20villages%20while%20the%20elderly%20men%20were%20mostly%20present%20at%20the%20protest%20sites.%20This%20way%20they%20ensured%20that%20there%20was%20no%20compromise%20in%20their%20farm%20produce%20while%20they%20were%20protesting%20to%20save%20their%20future%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESymbolism%20also%20plays%20an%20important%20role%20in%20such%20protests.%20Similar%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1007334%2Framachandra-guha-what-todays-farm-protests-share-with-vallabhbhai-patels-bardoli-satyagraha%5C%22%3EBardoli%C2%A0peasant%20satyagraha%20of%201928%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20the%20women%20dressed%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekhadi%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%20too%20were%20seen%20to%20have%20a%20specific%20dress%20code%20(salwar%20kameez%20and%20yellow%20dupatta).%20This%20highlighted%20unity%20and%20their%20resolve%20to%20affect%20change%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20movement%20where%20the%20leaders%20were%20overwhelmingly%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20targets%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work%3A%20A%20lesson%20for%20the%20political%20opposition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECreating%20targets%20through%20coercive%20legal%20action%2C%20enabled%20by%20brute%20electoral%20majority%2C%20produce%20strong%20emotive%20effects%20and%20have%20serious%20follow-on%20effects%20on%20how%20economies%20and%20societies%20function.%20If%20any%20sovereign%20passes%20laws%20that%20specifically%20create%20targets%2C%20or%20group-based%20markers%2C%20it%20could%20make%20space%20for%20a%20subsequent%20division%20in%20public%20opinion%20with%20one%20group%E2%80%99s%20views%20set%20against%20another%E2%80%99s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20only%20wish%20the%20Indian%20political%20opposition%20at%20this%20point%20of%20time%2C%20particularly%20in%20an%20election%20year%2C%20anchored%20by%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20would%20sooner%20realise%20this%20%E2%80%93%20and%20work%20towards%20harnessing%20the%20potential%20embedded%20in%20the%20design%2C%20social%20psychology%2C%20and%20political%20effectiveness%20of%20protest%20movements%20and%20street-based%20agitation%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20disappointing%20to%20see%20how%20even%20the%20decision%20to%20mass%20suspend%20MPs%20that%20caused%20millions%20of%20people%20to%20be%20not%20even%20represented%20in%20Parliament%20didn%E2%80%99t%20trigger%20any%20major%2C%20aggressive%20protests%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Delhi%20or%20otherwise%20by%20opposition%20MPs.%20Social%20media%20rants%2C%20virtual%20protests%20and%20op-eds%20have%20little%20meaning%20in%20fighting%20a%20state%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmodi-governmentality-similar-to-british-raj-s-755088.html%5C%22%3Ethat%20acts%20with%20impunity%20and%20in%20a%20manner%20consistent%20with%20a%20Hobbesian%20form%20of%20absolutist%20state%20%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERealising%20and%20harnessing%20%E2%80%98people%E2%80%99s%20power%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20politics%20of%20opposition%20may%20learn%20from%20recent%20protest%20movements%20to%20recognise%20how%20sustained%20people-based%20mass%20social%20movements%20through%20bottom-up%2C%20grassroot%20level%20networks%20can%20help%20mobilising%20resistance%20against%20authoritarian%20regimes%20and%20progressively%20(re)instate%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%20%E2%80%93%20while%20fighting%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eby%3C%2Fem%3E%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpinjra-tod-arrest-delhi-police-jafrabad%5C%22%3EOne%20can%20recall%20how%20arrests%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20women%20social%20activists%20Devangna%20Kalita%2C%20Natasha%20Narwal%2C%20Sudha%20Bharadwaj%20(to%20name%20a%20few)%2C%20are%20instances%20of%20a%20conscious%20attempt%20to%20sanction%20(arrest)%20dissent%20by%20the%20Modi%20government.%20Authoritarian%20regimes%20do%20so%20by%20practicing%20a%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eby%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%20where%20most%20decentralised%20social%20movements%20are%20countered%20vehemently%20(even%20by%20force)%20through%20institutional%20sanctions.%20Legal%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20courts%2C%20the%20police%20do%20everything%20in%20their%20power%20to%20suppress%20civic%20freedoms%20and%20liberties%20%E2%80%93%20including%20a%20basic%20right%20to%20peacefully%20protest%20against%20an%20act%2C%20or%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Econventional%20focus%20on%20building%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20often%20leave%20many%20citizens%20feeling%20disempowered%2C%20being%20expected%20to%20wait%20till%20%E2%80%9Call-important%20institutions%E2%80%9D%20reform%2C%20while%20they%20continue%20to%20be%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20oppression%20from%20those%20very%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20can%20one%20do%20when%20such%20institutions-meant%20to%20protect%20and%20safeguard%20liberties%20and%20a%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%20are%20so%20hollowed%20that%20they%20have%20become%20the%20primary%20tools%20for%20its%20very%20subversion%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20strengthen%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Ewhat%20we%20require%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20focus%20on%20strengthening%20%3Cem%3Epeople%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20not%20institutions.%20The%20INDIA%20bloc%20must%20realise%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20warrants%20a%20difficult%2C%20dangerous%20task%20of%20developing%20grassroots-based%20community%20organisation%20at%20a%20very%20decentralised%20level%2C%20often%20through%20informal%20networks%20outside%20established%20institutions.%20An%20action%2C%20sustaining%20resistance%20to%20authoritarianism%20through%20non-violent%20protests%2C%20marches%2C%20boycotts%2C%20strikes%2C%20as%20well%20as%20through%20community-based%20initiatives%20intervening%20at%20a%20local%20level%20to%20improve%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20rights-based%20legislations%20have%20often%20yielded%20the%20most%20transformation%20socio-political%20change%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Ein%20strengthening%20the%20state-citizen%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20allowing%20greater%20agency%20and%20accountability%20mechanisms%20for%20the%20citizen%20to%20keep%20the%20accumulative%20power%20of%20the%20state%20in%20check.%20Illustratively%2C%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20(2005)%20was%20a%20culmination%20of%20sustained%20collective%20action%20from%20organisations%20like%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20(MKSS)%20and%20National%20Campaign%20for%20People%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Information%20(NCPRI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20The%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20and%20Other%20Traditional%20Forest%20Dwellers%20(Recognition%20of%20Forest%20Rights)%20Act%20of%202006%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Ehelped%20acknowledge%20the%20rights%20of%20forest-dwelling%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20India.%20The%20making%20of%20the%20act%20mapped%20out%20a%20dense%20interplay%20between%20different%20actors%20in%20the%20drafting%20process.%20Social%20activists%20from%20the%20Campaign%20for%20Survival%20and%20Dignity%20(CSD)%20helped%20raise%20enough%20voice%20to%20convince%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs%20to%20consider%20drafting%20a%20new%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20NGREGA%20(2006)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Esaw%20an%20intense%20interaction%20between%20different%20state%20and%20non-state%20actors%3C%2Fa%3E%20(involving%20members%20of%20the%20civil%20society)%20that%20helped%20in%20actualising%20a%20legislation%20providing%20an%20opportunity%20for%20even%20the%20socially%20and%20culturally%20marginalised%20to%20develop%20new%20forms%20of%20claims%20to%20the%20local%20state%20apparatus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENandini%20Nayak%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feprints.soas.ac.uk%2F14020%2F%5C%22%3E2012%20thesis%3C%2Fa%3E%20provides%20a%20fascinating%20account%20of%20activism%20around%20NREGA%20in%20rural%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20that%20allowed%20Bhil%20Adivasis%20a%20chance%20to%20engage%20in%20and%20secure%20livelihood%20opportunities%20directly%20from%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20movement%20in%20the%20US%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20another%20such%20example%2C%20now%20witnessing%20a%20global%20reckoning.%20The%20movement%20made%20citizens%20question%20the%20role%20and%20acts%20of%20police%20against%20a%20minority%20and%20raised%20a%20collective%20effort%20for%20exploring%20new%2C%20more%20decentralised%20solutions%20primarily%20through%20community-driven%20initiatives%20to%20limit%20a%20pre-existing%2C%20dominant%20role%20of%20police%20(criminalising%20all%20behaviour)%20for%20improving%20the%20daily%20lives%20of%20all%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistory%20in%20different%20times%20and%20context%20has%20therefore%20shown%20how%2C%20even%20in%20most%20established%20democracies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-rule-of-law-by-peoples-power-855207.html%5C%22%3Ea%20failure%20to%20have%20formal%20institutions%20safeguarding%20rule%20of%20law%20is%20best%20substituted%20with%20an%20active%2C%20more%20aware%20and%20better%20organised%20citizenry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20An%20engagement%20like%20this%20cannot%20be%20legislated%20for%2C%20nor%20imitated%20from%20one%20city%20to%20another.%20People%20need%20to%20collectively%20build%20it%20bottom%20up%20in%20their%20own%20organic%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%E2%80%99s%20power%20can%20not%20only%20help%20substitute%20a%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eby%20%3C%2Fem%3Elaw%20with%20the%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%20but%20do%20so%20in%20a%20more%20sustained%20manner%20while%20championing%20democratic%20processes%20and%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20at%20least%20three%20ways%20this%20can%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFirst%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20such%20demonstrated%20people%E2%80%99s-power%20can%20help%20neutralise%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctop-down%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20placed%20on%20courts%20and%20the%20police%20by%20the%20executive.%20Even%20compromised%20institutions%20can%20be%20forced%20into%20discharging%20their%20duties%20in%20accordance%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20law-%20see%20how%20the%20murder%20charges%20were%20levied%20on%20cops%20involved%20in%20George%20Floyd%E2%80%99s%20killing%20as%20massive%20protests%20gained%20momentum%20to%20make%20the%20executive%20authorities%20to%20act%20swiftly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESecondly%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20people%20power%20based%20social%20movements%20allow%20an%20organic%20creation%20of%20alternative%20spaces%20that%20help%20shape%20a%20society%20where%20a%20rule%20of%20law%20can%20be%20respected.%20Any%20act%20of%20civil%20disobedience%20of%20course%20needs%20to%20have%20a%20strategic%20purpose%20and%20need%20some%20disciplining%20too%20for%20the%20engaged%20people%20to%20understand%20that%20the%20act%20of%20disobedience%20is%20done%20not%20with%20the%20intention%20to%20reject%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20but%20rather%20see%20it%20as%20a%20means%20of%20(re)establishing%20it%2C%20for%20a%20more%20just%20and%20progressive%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20%3Cem%3Ethird%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Epeople%E2%80%99s%20power%20can%20help%20bring%20even%20the%20most%20brutal%20authoritarian%20leaderships%20to%20be%20defeated%20with%20far-reaching%20consequences%20that%20could%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20otherwise.%20Public%20discussion%2C%20collective%20deliberation%20and%20social%20processes%20of%20participatory%20engagement%20opens%20citizens%E2%80%99%20minds%20to%20a%20more%20progressive%20idea%20of%20society%20that%20looks%20at%20a%20different%20way%20of%20doing%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20similar%20progressive%20views%20and%20thoughts%20need%20to%20better%20organise%20themselves%20today%2C%20learn%20to%20connect%20and%20engage%20with%20one%20another%20not%20on%20social%20media%20alone%20but%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20Over%20time%2C%20as%20people%20build%20mutual%20trust%2C%20gain%20the%20confidence%20and%20conviction%20both%20in%20themselves%20and%20in%20collective%20propriety%2C%20it%20allows%20new%20coalitions%20to%20be%20formed%20and%20ultimately%20be%20(cap)able%20to%20be%20more%20confrontational%20with%20the%20authoritarian%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20is%20the%20Chipko%20Movement%20of%201970s%3B%20the%20Anna%20Hazare%20Anti-Corruption%20Movement%20in%20early%202000s%3B%20the%20movement%20for%20stringent%20deterrence%20and%20sanctions%20in%20crimes%20against%20women%20after%20the%20Nirbhaya%20gang-rape%20case%2C%20all%2C%20reflect%20the%20might%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20power%2C%20which%2C%20through%20social%20movements%20and%20rights-based%20movements%20can%20bring%20reformative%20changes%20in%20the%20existing%20political%20and%20social%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20ever%2C%20harnessing%20this%20power%20is%20critical%20for%20the%20Indian%20political%20opposition%20in%20reinstating%20a%20rule%20%3Cem%3Eof%3C%2Fem%3E%20law%2C%20demonstrating%20the%20resilience%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20against%20any%20given%20regime%20which%20wishes%20to%20weaken%20that.%20As%20of%20now%2C%20in%20what%20is%20consequentially%20going%20to%20be%20a%20defining%20national%20election%20in%202024%2C%20the%20INDIA%20opposition%20bloc%20looks%20more%20lost%20than%20aware%20of%20these%20socio-historical%20realities%20and%20their%20political%20effectiveness-in%20resisting%20and%20taking%20on%20larger%2Fbigger%20political%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704271240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03132615%2FDM1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftrucker-protests-are-another-instance-of-the-success-of-street-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20political%20opposition%20should%20take%20lessons%20from%20people's%20movements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftrucker-protests-are-another-instance-of-the-success-of-street-politics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ryanair%20lashes%20out%20at%20online%20'pirates'%20after%20airline%20removed%20from%20booking%20sites%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704269940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F768x432%2Fskynews-ryanair-plane_6292411.jpg%3F20230921102917%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fryanair-lashes-out-at-online-pirates-after-airline-removed-from-booking-sites-including-bookingcom-and-kayak-13041325%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ryanair%20has%20warned%20its%20business%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20hit%20in%20the%20short%20term%20after%20a%20string%20of%20online%20travel%20agents%20removed%20the%20airline%20from%20their%20online%20listings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fryanair-lashes-out-at-online-pirates-after-airline-removed-from-booking-sites-including-booking-com-and-kayak-13041325%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fryanair-lashes-out-at-online-pirates-after-airline-removed-from-booking-sites-including-booking-com-and-kayak-13041325%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A